{"type":"message","id":"1bd3efdd","parentId":"7c082137","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:38:55.008Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_np0uzf6s54p1_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 033814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions, the most concrete next step is implementing the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n   - Identifies invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) content\r\n   - Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory and look at the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc to understand the spec better.\r\n\r\nActually, since I'm a stateless discontinuous agent, I should just take one concrete action. The most logical next step is to start implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Create an initial TIC classifier script (PowerShell since we're in a Windows environment)\r\n2. This script should analyze the pulse logs and classify content as invariant/variant\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that will:\r\n1. Read the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Identify patterns across them\r\n3. Classify content as invariant or variant\r\n4. Attempt prediction of next pulse\r\n\r\nI'll create `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` as the initial implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. Need to implement the classifier to analyze pulse logs and test invariant/variant classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate initial TIC classifier PowerShell script that reads pulse logs, identifies invariant patterns across sessions, classifies content, and attempts next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Validates: compression = causal discovery hypothesis\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,           # Number of pulse logs to analyze\r\n    [int]$MinOccurrence = 3,        # Minimum occurrences for invariant status\r\n    [double]$MinInvariance = 0.7    # 70% threshold for invariance\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n\r\n# Paths\r\n$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n$OutputDir = \"tic\"\r\n$LogPattern = \"pulse_*.md\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Lookback: $Lookback pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"MinOccurrence: $MinOccurrence\"\r\nWrite-Host \"MinInvariance: $MinInvariance\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Ensure output directory exists\r\nif (-not (Test-Path $OutputDir)) {\r\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $OutputDir | Out-Null\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Get pulse log files sorted by name (chronological)\r\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($LogFiles.Count -lt 3) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] Need at least 3 pulse logs, found $($LogFiles.Count)\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs to analyze\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Extract content tokens from each pulse\r\n$pulseData = @()\r\n$allTokens = @{}\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $LogFiles.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $file = $LogFiles[$i]\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract significant tokens (words > 3 chars, excluding common words)\r\n    $stopWords = @(\"the\",\"and\",\"for\",\"are\",\"but\",\"not\",\"you\",\"all\",\"can\",\"her\",\"was\",\"one\",\"our\",\"out\",\"was\",\"has\",\"had\",\"was\",\"this\",\"that\",\"with\",\"from\",\"they\",\"will\",\"would\",\"there\",\"their\",\"what\",\"about\",\"which\",\"when\",\"make\",\"like\",\"time\",\"just\",\"know\",\"take\",\"people\",\"into\",\"year\",\"your\",\"good\",\"some\",\"could\",\"them\",\"see\",\"other\",\"than\",\"then\",\"now\",\"look\",\"only\",\"come\",\"its\",\"over\",\"such\",\"also\",\"back\",\"after\",\"use\",\"two\",\"how\",\"our\",\"work\",\"first\",\"well\",\"way\",\"even\",\"new\",\"want\",\"because\",\"any\",\"these\",\"give\",\"day\",\"most\",\"us\")\r\n    \r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content.ToLower(), '\\b[a-z]{4,}\\b') | \r\n        Where-Object { $stopWords -notcontains $_.Value } |\r\n        ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | \r\n        Sort-Object | \r\n        Get-Unique\r\n    \r\n    $pulseData += @{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Tokens = $tokens\r\n        Index = $i\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $allTokens.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n            $allTokens[$token] = @()\r\n        }\r\n        $allTokens[$token] += $i\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Classify tokens as INVARIANT vs VARIANT\r\n$invariantTokens = @{}\r\n$variantTokens = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $allTokens.Keys) {\r\n    $occurrences = $allTokens[$token]\r\n    $count = $occurrences.Count\r\n    $span = ($LogFiles.Count - 1) / ($count -\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:38:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337935007}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff1f9165","parentId":"1bd3efdd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:39:05.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran and proposed a mutation to create a TIC classifier script. The mutation was partially applied (Python parser says `new_len=2793` for the `initial` file). The output shows a proposed mutation that creates `tic/tic_classifier.ps1`. \n\nLet me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"4d71ac2ccc98154b6d33145d02d3c381f1c524c1ac61378dae006aa8a011116b"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 03:38**\n\n✅ **Pulse ran successfully.** The agent analyzed the current project state and identified the next logical experiment: **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression)** — a classifier to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis (that compression and causal discovery are the same problem).\n\n**Proposed Mutation:** Create `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` — a script that reads the last 20 pulse logs, extracts tokens, classifies them as **invariant** (stable across pulses) vs **variant** (changing), and attempts next-pulse prediction. Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction.\n\n**Current project status:**\n- Phase 0 & 1 complete\n- COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY identified as core insight\n- TIC experiment is the pending next step\n\nThe mutation appears to be staged but not fully committed. If you want to apply it, let me know — or I can push it forward."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2385,"output":281,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774337935009}}
